        "para_id": "p15",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Influencer Marketing",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "Dutch influencers generally wish to comply with the rules (evidenced by the 2,200 certified influencers registered a few months ago) but they prefer to express themselves in creative ways that work for their audience and advertisers."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 14014,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "It is more effective for Member States to conduct national research into how their consumers engage with social media. For example, Dutch studies have shown how children perceive online content and how quickly they can recognise whether something is commercial. In the Netherlands, the hashtag #ad has lost much of its effectiveness, but other disclosures have proven to be more successful. Dutch influencers generally wish to comply with the rules (evidenced by the 2,200 certified influencers registered a few months ago) but they prefer to express themselves in creative ways that work for their audience and advertisers.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s5",
          "section_path": [
            "Dark patterns:",
            "Influencer Marketing:"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 98,
          "char_len": 624
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p16",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Influencer Marketing",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "influencers to be transparent when engaging in commercial communication"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 7558,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Because national markets can identify such trends and adapt more quickly, self-regulation remains an effective and flexible tool. We therefore recommend not making EU disclosure and labelling requirements too prescriptive. Member States should retain the discretion to determine, through self-regulation or national law, what forms of disclosure are most appropriate for the consumers in their countries. Instead, the DFA should provide harmonised principles requiring influencers to be transparent when engaging in commercial communication and to consider the impact of their content on viewers (consumers).",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s5",
          "section_path": [
            "Dark patterns:",
            "Influencer Marketing:"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 84,
          "char_len": 608
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p17",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Influencer Marketing",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "influencer marketing"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 11202,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Beyond the Netherlands, several Member States have already introduced sector initiatives to improve compliance and transparency in influencer marketing. The Dutch certification programme for influencers ensures they are aware of both statutory and self-regulatory advertising rules. Similar initiatives exist in France, Belgium, Spain, and Romania, and all are part of Ad Ethics, a European umbrella initiative for influencer education. Early results in the Netherlands are promising: compliance with advertising rules increased from 25% to 60% after certification.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s5",
          "section_path": [
            "Dark patterns:",
            "Influencer Marketing:"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 77,
          "char_len": 565
        }
